questionRound.0.question.9.answer: You just need to know what the person after you will choose. I started from the last person - that one was always easy because one of their rows was always noticeably higher than the other. Then I predicted what people would choose based on the idea that they also used this type of logic.
I went basically off what I would choose if I were the other colors in the game  and what would be the most beneifical as well as logical choice.

After the first game  I figured the last player is easily at advantage when it comes to deciding his best choices. So from there i moved on to monitor the player who  depended on the last player and moved on again till i got to the player who i depended on. I could then make my best choice from there

I chose my answers based on what I thought the next (or last) player would choose. Based on what the first player chose  I guessed what the last player would choose and used his answer to choose mine.

If i was first one to go then i would check how the last person will respond to get maximum points. The person before the last one will respond according to the last person's response to get maximum points. In the same way  every person's points depends on the person who is playing next to them. So I tried to guess what the person next to me will play and decided my option accordingly.
anticipate the end squares and then evaluate backwards.
I looked at previous decisions made and chose accordingly.

Because there is only one optimal choice for the last player in this program's setup. so just figure out what he would choose and deduct backward step by step  you can solve the only one optimal solution for all the players.

I tried to think backwards from how my move would affect other players. However upon completion I should have added the level of thinking to include how the next player (if I acted first) could utilize my information to maximize gains for myself; rather  than looking to see how all players after me could cooperate and maximize. I made the mistake of thinking if i acted first cooperatively that no players would defect and attempt to maximize.
I used backwards induction to determine the players' moves in reverse.  This strategy worked as all of the moves were rational.
